---
description: |
  Project structure and organization patterns for Vue.js application with CoreUI, services, and modular architecture.
globs:
  - src/**/*
  - src/components/**/*
  - src/services/**/*
  - src/store/**/*
  - src/router/**/*
  - src/assets/**/*
alwaysApply: true
rules:
  # Directory Structure
  - `/src/components/` - Reusable components
    - `/common/` - Shared/common components
    - `/pages/` - Page-specific components organized by feature
  - `/src/containers/` - Container components
  - `/src/services/` - API services and utilities
  - `/src/store/` - Vuex store modules
  - `/src/router/` - Router configuration
  - `/src/assets/` - Static assets (images, styles)
  - `/src/mixins/` - Vue mixins for shared logic

  # Component Organization
  - Create reusable components in `/src/components/common/`
  - Create page-specific components in `/src/components/pages/`
  - Organize components by feature/domain
  - Use proper component naming conventions

  # Service Layer
  - Use `/src/services/` for API services and utilities
  - Follow the established axios instance patterns (pfAxios, dsAxios)
  - Use the established interceptor patterns
  - Implement proper error handling in services

  # Store Organization
  - Use `/src/store/` for Vuex store modules
  - Follow the established module structure
  - Use namespaced modules for better organization
  - Keep store modules focused on specific domains

  # Router Configuration
  - Use `/src/router/` for router configuration
  - Follow the established route structure with meta properties
  - Use route guards for authentication and permissions
  - Implement proper route parameters and query handling

  # Asset Organization
  - Use `/src/assets/` for static assets
  - Organize images by type/feature
  - Use SCSS for styling with proper structure
  - Follow the established asset import patterns

  # File Naming Conventions
  - Components: PascalCase (e.g., `UserProfile.vue`)
  - Files: kebab-case (e.g., `user-profile.vue`)
  - Variables: camelCase
  - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
  - CSS classes: kebab-case

  # Cross-References
  - Vue patterns: `02-technical/01-vue-patterns.mdc`
  - Vuex patterns: `02-technical/02-vuex-patterns.mdc`
  - API standards: `02-technical/05-api-standards.mdc`
  - UI components: `02-technical/06-ui-component-rules.mdc`
